The paper focuses on the security of IoT devices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of machine learning for both attack and countermeasures suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the physical and mathematical tamper-proofing of PUF architectures, which may fall under the categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
